  <title>Secret.SchemaAttributeType</title>
  <p>The type of an attribute in a <link xref="Secret.Schema"/>. Attributes are stored as strings
in the Secret Service, and the attribute types simply define standard ways
to store integer and boolean values as strings.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>SchemaAttributeType.STRING</code></title>
  <p>a utf-8 string attribute</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>SchemaAttributeType.INTEGER</code></title>
  <p>an integer attribute, stored as a decimal</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>SchemaAttributeType.BOOLEAN</code></title>
  <p>a boolean attribute, stored as 'true' or 'false'</p>
</item>
